title: Independent candidate Dawar Kundi wins NA-43 election
content:
DERA ISMAIL KHAN, Feb 10 (APP):Independent candidate Dawar Khan Kundi has won the National Assembly election from NA-43, Tank cum DI Khan by securing 63,556 votes in a tough competition.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer, his runner-up was Jamiat Ulema Islam Fazl (JUI-F) candidate Asad Mahmood who bagged 62,730 votes. Overall voters turnout remained 43.32 percent.
This constituency comprising Tank District and some areas of Dera Ismail Khan District had a total of 392,214 registered voters including 214,789 men and 177, 425 women. In the recent election, a total of 169,896 voters including 104,867 men and 65,029 women utilized their right to vote.
